Packages
- group classes together by shared functionality
- access control
- to create : package package1.labs;
- . to create hierarchy
- to compile and run a java file, be in folder of root of package
: javac codingnomads/examples/oop/inheritance/CarController.java
- to run : java codingnoamds/examples/oop/inheritance/CarController

Import packages
- allows use of elements of that package
- done at beginning of a file
: import package1.package2.Classname;
- still restrictions on members with certain access modifiers
- import all classes in a package
: import package1.package2.*;
- import so you don't have to write rootPackage.subPackage.className inside the method body